---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AudienceSplit from '../components/AudienceSplit.astro';
import AnalysisSequence from '../components/AnalysisSequence.astro';
import RoleIssueCrosswalk from '../components/RoleIssueCrosswalk.astro';
import LibraryIndex from '../components/LibraryIndex.astro';
import DevelopmentsList from '../components/DevelopmentsList.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Auto Wage Law" description="A disciplined system for mapping dealership work, pay rules, legal tests, records, and consequences.">
  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="home-hero shell">
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <p class="eyebrow">Dealership wage-and-hour analysis</p>
        <p>California + federal · source checked July 2026</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <h1>Map the pay system before you judge the result.</h1>
          <p class="lede">A disciplined wage-and-hour review separates the work, the pay rule, the legal test, the records, and the consequence.</p>
          <div class="button-row">
            <a class="button" href="/analysis-map/">Open the analysis map</a>
            <a class="button button--quiet" href="#role-crosswalk">Start with a dealership role</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside>
          <span class="hero-index">METHOD / 01–06</span>
          <p><strong>Facts → Classify → Measure → Test → Verify → Act</strong></p>
          <p>A pay label cannot select its own legal rule. One record cannot prove more than the event it captures.</p>
        </aside>
      </div>
      <AnalysisSequence />
    </section>

    <section id="role-crosswalk" class="section shell">
      <RoleIssueCrosswalk />
    </section>

    <section class="section section--mist">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <div><p class="eyebrow">Choose the side of the counter</p><h2>Two paths. One set of pay records.</h2></div>
          <p>The questions change by role. The underlying evidence usually does not.</p>
        </div>
        <AudienceSplit />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section shell">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Open law library</p><h2>The collision points.</h2></div>
        <p>Move from the pay system to the wage-and-hour issue without losing the dealership context.</p>
      </div>
      <LibraryIndex />
    </section>

    <section class="section section--mist release-strip">
      <div class="shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <div><p class="eyebrow">Developments</p><h2>What moved.</h2></div>
          <a class="text-link" href="/developments/">View the release log</a>
        </div>
        <DevelopmentsList />
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .home-hero { padding-block: 2rem var(--space-9); }
  .hero-meta { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 1rem; border-bottom: var(--rule); padding-bottom: 0.8rem; }
  .hero-meta p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-muted); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 9fr) minmax(14rem, 3fr); gap: var(--space-7); padding-top: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.5rem); }
  .hero-grid h1 { max-width: 66rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: clamp(3.35rem, 7.6vw, 7.4rem); line-height: 0.86; }
  .hero-grid h1 { color: var(--color-ink); }
  .hero-grid .lede { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .hero-grid aside { align-self: end; border-top: 3px solid var(--color-ink); padding-top: 1rem; }
  .hero-grid aside p { margin: 0.8rem 0 0; color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .hero-grid aside strong { color: var(--color-ink); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.74rem; }
  .hero-index { color: var(--color-cobalt-dark); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 600; }
  @media (max-width: 50rem) { .home-hero { padding-top: 1.25rem; } .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .hero-grid aside { display: none; } .hero-meta p:last-child { display: none; } }
</style>
